
[1]dogmatical

   DOGMATIC, DOGMATICAL, a.

   1. Pertaining to a dogma, or to settled opinion.

   2. Positive; magisterial; asserting or disposed to assert with
   authority or with overbearing and arrogance; applied to persons; as a
   dogmatic schoolman or philosopher.

   3. Positive; asserted with authority; authoritative; as a dogmatical
   opinion.

   4. Arrogant; overbearing in asserting and maintaining opinions.
